Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.44,0:00:09.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kagami Yoshimizu Theater"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.91,0:00:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3rd year, class B...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.08,0:00:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Kuroi!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.20,0:00:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.40,0:00:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The ambiguous 3cm? Does that \Nmean it's plushy? Wait!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wrapping is a uniform, \Nargh, it's not an act, pooh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.58,0:00:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotta do your best, gotta just do it{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.29,0:00:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's time to catch 'n' release, eek{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.91,0:00:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Between sweat (whoop) Sweat (whoop){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.95,0:00:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Darlin', darlin', freeze! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.59,0:00:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kinda lethargic, something's kinda comin' out{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.91,0:00:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I love you... Oh wait, one \Nof those was different{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worrywarts, high metal bars {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.12,0:00:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tasty thoughts... And that's enough!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.91,0:00:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heated body of that flying you-know-who{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.70,0:00:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's what you call a normal girlie{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.22,0:00:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Am I the only one surprised? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.62,0:00:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seconds on pork-bone broth \Nramen with wire-hard noodles{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.77,0:00:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Da da da da da {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.94,0:00:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pom-poms cheer squad{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.66,0:00:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's get cherry pie {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happy fun welcoming party {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.01,0:00:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look up! Sensation{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.45,0:00:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah! Feeling of existence, \Ndot dot small planet{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.41,0:00:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Collided and it melted away, in total awe{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.08,0:01:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go all out to sing, shi-ranger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.97,0:01:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Take it away! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.00,0:01:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I should be the one who'll \Nbe laughing in the end{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.50,0:01:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because I have the sailor suit \N← This is my conclusion{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.51,0:01:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's only Monday! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.70,0:01:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Already in a bad mood? What to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.45,0:01:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I really prefer the summer outfits \N← kya! Wah! Good! (cute!) < 3{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.14,0:01:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Until we approach 3 pixels, \Nno hesitations please ★{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.34,0:01:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do your best, be energetic {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.02,0:01:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My darlin', darlin' please! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.98,0:01:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, thanks for the meal today!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.78,0:01:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, you're free to \Nhave something like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.62,0:01:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.24,0:01:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.87,0:01:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the eggs are tasty, it \Nmakes you feel kinda happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.91,0:01:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.96,0:01:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The price of gas is up two \Nyen compared to yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.04,0:01:53.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I had filled up yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.63,0:01:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are even generous people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.13,0:01:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,picky down to each yen \Nconcerning the price of gas?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.80,0:01:57.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Yonder Here"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.80,0:02:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, they're turning the book I \Nlent you the other day into a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.47,0:02:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I'm not going to buy the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.26,0:02:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami, your information is so old.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.18,0:02:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I reserved the limited edition the \Nmoment the info first came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.89,0:02:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bought the DVD box set for the \Nanime and various goods as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.98,0:02:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you've gotten hooked on \Nthe series more than I have!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.02,0:02:17.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can get hooked more than \Nthe one who told you about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.32,0:02:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis Yui is the type that \Nbuys a car like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.95,0:02:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,based on influence from others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.16,0:02:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A car?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.91,0:02:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. When I lent her manga about races.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.83,0:02:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really got surprised back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.54,0:02:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared of the energy \Nthat hobbies can create!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.29,0:02:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The game last night made three wins in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.29,0:02:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! It's the beginning of a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.63,0:02:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they can keep winning like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.38,0:02:36.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,What is she talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.38,0:02:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the playoffs, even the \NJapan Series, are in reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.88,0:02:39.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it's about professional baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.47,0:02:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an incomparable, \Nwonderful winning streak!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.05,0:02:40.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Our teacher is heavily into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.89,0:02:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, speaking of baseball,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.30,0:02:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The famous poet Shiki Masaoka \Napparently loved baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.89,0:02:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that he played catcher \Nuntil illness forced him to retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.02,0:02:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Playing upon his childhood name, Noboru,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.57,0:02:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he used as his poet's title the kanji \Nfor baseball, and read it as "Noball."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.28,0:02:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.99,0:03:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The winner of the Major Leagues is \Ncalled the World Champions, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.16,0:03:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was reminded of it by the Japan Series.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.53,0:03:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Come to think of it, it's \Nonly within the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.95,0:03:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, start talking about "World" \Nafter you defeat our team, I say!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.58,0:03:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.34,0:03:17.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The center of the universe is in Chiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.34,0:03:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's really getting worked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty smelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.55,0:03:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there you are. Kagami! Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Konata.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.47,0:03:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me how to do this problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.25,0:03:29.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is unusual,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.64,0:03:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for you to be asking a \Nquestion about your studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.31,0:03:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some of these problems are pretty hard, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.23,0:03:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's because those are problems
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.78,0:03:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the quiz game at the arcade.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.99,0:03:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not good at the general \Neducation questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.57,0:03:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you go again...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.32,0:03:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, why not put more effort \Ninto your academic studies?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.83,0:03:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got entrance exams coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may be like that over here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.08,0:03:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but over there I'm called a "Sage" and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.33,0:03:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, why don't you just enroll \Nyourself in that Whatsit Academy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.96,0:04:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so I'm a bit short on sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.34,0:04:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How late were you up playing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.24,0:04:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you always \Ngo to sleep at 11, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.14,0:04:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.97,0:04:07.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's early, or rather...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.14,0:04:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kids that sleep, grow ★" I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.47,0:04:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I thought stuff like that \Nas I was watching Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Yu-{\i1}chan{\i0}, you sleep a lot, \Nyet you haven't grown so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.90,0:04:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Sis told me! I'm \Nconcerned about it too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:22.95,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"That night, around 9 PM"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.95,0:04:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, pardon me for calling so late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Kobayakawa. Is \Nthis the Iwasaki residence?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.03,0:04:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, I'd like to \Nspeak with Minami-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.62,0:04:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she's already asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.50,0:04:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did she always go to sleep this early?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.98,0:04:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Pittan la la moji pittan! ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.69,0:04:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're singing very happily there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.65,0:05:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes. Yes, somehow, \NI think it's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, I'll relay the \Ninformation to Dad as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.78,0:05:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, after the ceremony. Yes, right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.66,0:05:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no, nothing of the sort...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.02,0:05:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, seriously... I'm still a minor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, that's not it, \Nit's nothing like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.84,0:05:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, then... yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.17,0:05:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Kagami...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.84,0:05:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you gesture, the other \Nside's not going to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.30,0:05:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that. I can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.85,0:05:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, with phone calls, \Nyou concentrate on the conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.89,0:05:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you can't help but stop \Nplaying games and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.91,0:05:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But for some reason, your hand \Nfeels a bit lonely when it's idle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.36,0:05:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know how that feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.94,0:05:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, as I was on the phone the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.19,0:05:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was using one of those rollers to get \Nrid of lint and stuff on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.74,0:05:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the ones that you roll around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.49,0:05:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you can get stuck in \Na rut with that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.53,0:05:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simple processes like meaningless doodles...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.54,0:05:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but the instant the \Nphone conversation is over,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.71,0:05:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you lose motivation to \Ncontinue stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.42,0:06:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But a floor where only one patch \Nis clean seems kind of sad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.75,0:06:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can just finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.59,0:06:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The passion to continue ends \Nalong with the conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.05,0:06:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you leave it alone in the end?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.30,0:06:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's pretty smelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.10,0:06:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's good once in a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.14,0:06:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. ___ky. Po___.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.23,0:06:22.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I did stuff like that back \Nwhen I was in grade school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.93,0:06:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, are you still a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.19,0:06:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, speaking about what you did as a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,didn't you yell "Bread factory!" \NWhile you stirred yogurt and stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.74,0:06:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bread factory?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.95,0:06:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, never heard of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.62,0:06:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.33,0:06:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what was that just now? A bread factory?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.42,0:06:45.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be embarrassed, you \Ncan say it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.42,0:06:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.92,0:06:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That game I lent you during \Nthe first trimester...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.84,0:06:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone else wants to \Nplay it, so give it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.30,0:06:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. You mean that little one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.22,0:06:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Come to think of it, \NI lent her a couple too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.52,0:06:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll get them back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.81,0:06:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, you're amazing, Hiiragi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.85,0:07:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.60,0:07:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I found a couple games the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.81,0:07:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I don't remember who I borrowed from...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.11,0:07:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed that you can keep track.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.11,0:07:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are a couple of mine that \NI don't remember who I lent to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.90,0:07:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how lazy are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.45,0:07:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I think "The Rule of Forgetting \Nthe Lender" definitely applies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.12,0:07:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.45,0:07:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course there's no such thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.67,0:07:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.30,0:07:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Hiiragi? It's me, Misao!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.01,0:07:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, what do you wa--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.38,0:07:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit... You're pretty good, Po___mkin...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.76,0:07:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.80,0:07:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, it's nothing... Sorry, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.81,0:07:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.18,0:07:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.56,0:07:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.48,0:07:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I'd know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.81,0:07:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was something important...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's important, don't forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.60,0:07:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I checked the results for \Nthe Autumn Jumbo Lottery,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but none of them were winning tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it's not all that \Noften that you get a winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.80,0:07:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sent a lot of postcards too, but \NI didn't win any prizes either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, that's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.16,0:08:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's this hard to win,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.33,0:08:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I start to wonder if the \Npeople who sell these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.88,0:08:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or the editors, are cheating...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.05,0:08:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konata, you shouldn't doubt people like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.18,0:08:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good. I guess I'll \Ngo to sleep for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.39,0:08:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before that, I guess I'll go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.81,0:08:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say I have too much personal talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.02,0:08:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but that doesn't matter at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.90,0:08:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so sleepy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.70,0:08:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I feel so awake after \Ncracking a stupid joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.70,0:08:39.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Next day, late at night"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good at night after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need to go to the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.83,0:08:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I should go to sleep \Nwhile I'm feeling sleepy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.75,0:08:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.13,0:08:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so sleepy, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.76,0:08:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does the cold wake me up \Nthe instant I get in my futon?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.35,0:09:01.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"And yet the next night, late at night"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.39,0:09:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.56,0:09:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's warm tonight, so maybe \NI can get to sleep soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.27,0:09:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason, my feet feel really hot
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.19,0:09:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I can't get to sleep... Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.78,0:09:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I the only one that feels stuff like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.36,0:09:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.08,0:09:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotten to be the season where \Nroasted sweet potatoes taste good!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.87,0:09:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Kagami, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.54,0:09:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I know. I know, so don't say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.58,0:09:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want to have some?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.63,0:09:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.84,0:09:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you'll get fat, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.00,0:09:32.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You ended up saying it after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.21,0:09:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't help it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made eye contact with the guy selling them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.05,0:09:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd feel bad not buying any, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.76,0:09:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, those eyes that say to \Nyou, "I hope she buys some..."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.89,0:09:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'd be hurt if she didn't buy any..."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well, I see what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.14,0:09:48.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At Comiket, it's hard to put a \Nbook down if you make eye contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, when you talk, you never \Ncare about getting your points across.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.94,0:09:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, I'm talking about when I'm \Nbrowsing through various circles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.78,0:09:58.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you pick up a book \Nin front of the seller,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.11,0:10:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you feel bad about leaving for \Nanother table without buying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you put it down all the same, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.91,0:10:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.17,0:10:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, they've been adapting \Nmore light novels into anime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.41,0:10:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.33,0:10:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The novel that I lent you the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.21,0:10:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has turned into an anime three times already.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.46,0:10:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the new volume \Nis coming out soon, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.17,0:10:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the anime version, but I \Nhaven't read the novel yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.30,0:10:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It tires me out because \Nit's so full of words.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.05,0:10:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That again?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.43,0:10:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The games that you play \Nare even wordier, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.97,0:10:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's the case. It's so strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.60,0:10:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would help if they released all \Nof those books in gal-game form.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.84,0:10:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.65,0:10:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from that, I wonder when the \Nfourth anime season is going to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.82,0:10:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what? Is that some kind of plot device?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.58,0:10:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yu-{\i1}chan{\i0}, what are you up to over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lid... It always ends up crooked...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:10:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there are people like that out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.17,0:11:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those that are a bit awkward.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do it often?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.22,0:11:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. These cute faults that you \Nhave are so like Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.93,0:11:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. Sis, you really are amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.94,0:11:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, what should I do? It won't open now...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.82,0:11:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. I did it in the usual manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.07,0:11:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a problematic child...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.48,0:11:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bag won't open? Hand it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.70,0:11:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Sis, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.92,0:11:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.17,0:11:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:38.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we rip it from \Nthe jagged edge to open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.34,0:11:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, hold on... I'll open \Nit properly, so hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.80,0:11:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.22,0:11:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.56,0:11:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we use the jagged \Nedge, or open it with scissors?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's something about my pride...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.69,0:11:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like I've lost somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.57,0:12:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis... Is that a mosquito?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.07,0:12:06.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a mosquito.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it irritate you, just knowing \Nthat it's somewhere around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.74,0:12:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it hasn't done anything to you yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.62,0:12:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I know it's here, I can't \Nhelp but to make sure it's down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.62,0:12:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is what you call hunter's instincts!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.04,0:12:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just had a thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.62,0:12:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Yu-{\i1}chan {\i0}or I were to be asked \Nout by someone in our grade,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.47,0:12:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would that mean that guy \Nhas a Lolita complex?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the same grade,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.43,0:12:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you were to argue \Notherwise, you could...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.68,0:12:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this case, appearance weighs \Nheavily on the decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.73,0:12:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For instance, what if she was 30 but \Nlooked like she was in grade school?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.65,0:12:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand, in that case,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.03,0:12:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you could say that you favored older women...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.61,0:12:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a pretty deep theme there. \NIt's hard to determine the theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.53,0:12:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really are my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.95,0:12:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami would end up saying something \Nlike "I don't care which."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.79,0:12:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Dad, what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.42,0:12:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fell in love with Mom, \Nwho looked like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.42,0:13:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and love this daughter so much...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.63,0:13:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you have a Lolita \Ncomplex, right, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, hold on, you're mistaken there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.92,0:13:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like normal girls, not just young girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.72,0:13:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Sometimes I have a Lolita complex."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.64,0:13:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it depends on the character.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.31,0:13:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In either case, you're a good-for-nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.64,0:13:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you always get clingy with me, Dad,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.49,0:13:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but would you be acting the same \Nway even if I had been born a boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.40,0:13:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.78,0:13:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah. I've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.61,0:13:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you glad I'm a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.70,0:13:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what? I think the bath is ready now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.75,0:13:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go on ahead, Yu-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.41,0:13:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.76,0:13:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He shooed her away because he felt \Nbad about having her listen in!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.71,0:13:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.67,0:13:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom was really short, and she \Nknew you all her life, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.51,0:13:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't she like a gal-game character?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.43,0:13:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't she? Kanata was really \Ncute since she was a child!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.02,0:13:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that you were head-over-heels for her,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.85,0:13:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I wonder why Mom decided to marry you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.40,0:14:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I said, "Because you didn't look my way,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.07,0:14:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up as the gal-game \Nloving guy that you see here!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.53,0:14:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She went along with it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.07,0:14:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.57,0:14:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.16,0:14:10.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that extortion?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.91,0:14:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, that's not all, of \Ncourse. You know that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.20,0:14:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you were born, Konata, \NI was really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.62,0:14:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this mole looks a little \Nlike yours, Sou-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.76,0:14:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, she has your eyes, Kanata!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.59,0:14:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how you look at \Nit, she's our daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.49,0:14:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I hope that she grows a \Ndifferent way than either of us...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.05,0:14:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not like my height, or \NSou-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s personality...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's harsh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.89,0:14:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why are you suddenly \Ntalking about Kanata?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.35,0:14:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know much about Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.07,0:14:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konata, are you lonely \Nwithout your mother around?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.61,0:14:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. Dad, you alone \Nare rowdy enough for two,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.67,0:14:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and now Yu-{\i1}chan{\i0} is with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.95,0:14:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:15:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata... Konata has grown \Nup into a wonderful girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.25,0:15:04.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though she's a bit different from the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.25,0:15:05.30,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Short and has maniac knowledge"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.13,0:15:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,kind of normal you were hoping for.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.88,0:15:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Konata.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg of you, Konata, make \Nsure you don't die before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.76,0:15:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For now, I have no such intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.56,0:15:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.56,0:15:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata passed away early in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.06,0:15:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but she laughed at the end, \Nsaying that she was happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.27,0:15:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones that are left behind \Nare still a bit lonely,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.65,0:15:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'd like how I end my life \Nto be something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.11,0:15:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Laughing? How would you like to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.15,0:15:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... I'd like to be "{\i1}moe{\i0}-d" to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.53,0:15:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, I'm sure you'd never die a decent death.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.62,0:15:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.62,0:15:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bought a digital camera today \Nto use for work research...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.14,0:16:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while since I last came here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.98,0:16:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're persistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.60,0:16:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on... One more, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.60,0:16:07.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what they are doing right about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.36,0:16:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in the middle of a game!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.98,0:16:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, sure! Say cheese!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.82,0:16:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.78,0:16:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's go for one more!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.82,0:16:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've had enough, right? \NDad, you're being too clingy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.12,0:16:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so cold, Konata!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.08,0:16:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And here we are doing a memorial \Nphoto shoot with the new camera!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.62,0:16:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you said it was for reference?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.33,0:16:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so hard-headed, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.33,0:16:29.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... Sou-{\i1}kun {\i0}is still the same as ever...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.55,0:16:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One more shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.46,0:16:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, you never worried much \Nabout what others were thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.22,0:16:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.30,0:16:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch! That's so cruel, Konata!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.22,0:16:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.51,0:16:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly... He hasn't changed one bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.89,0:16:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.69,0:16:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Holding you is more and more like \Nthe feeling of holding Kanata...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.81,0:16:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes my heart race.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.40,0:16:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make such dangerous statements \Nwith your head held high!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.65,0:16:54.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom's troubles are such fond memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.90,0:16:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.20,0:16:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.62,0:16:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad may be like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.03,0:17:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but don't you stray away \Nand become a problem child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.95,0:17:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, by the way, Konata. That \Ngame from the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.71,0:17:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you finish it, tell \Nme how I can finish it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.33,0:17:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.58,0:17:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's much more difficult than I expected,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.96,0:17:12.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,But seeing that they play games as a family,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.96,0:17:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,though I'm sure I'm just choosing \Nthe wrong answer somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.96,0:17:14.47,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess they're doing well together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.47,0:17:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't quite get to the sex scene \Nwith the character I'm going after.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.93,0:17:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, hold on! What are you \Nmaking your daughter play?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.50,0:17:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if she's all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.22,0:17:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe your process of educating \Nher is mistaken, Sou-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.77,0:17:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why did Mom pick you, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.57,0:17:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you're just a perverted \Nold otaku with a Lolita complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.57,0:17:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, nobody would pick you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.15,0:17:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd go that far in saying it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.03,0:17:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really are harsh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.08,0:17:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.24,0:17:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, Kanata was \Na very perceptive person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.11,0:17:45.29,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, you always act like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.79,0:17:48.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I always start to forget...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.79,0:17:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she saw through it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.42,0:17:52.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,...why he was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.42,0:17:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that even a good- for-nothing like me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:58.47,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,...the one I decided to be with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...had one thing that I could \Nbe absolutely proud of.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.14,0:18:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing you were absolutely proud of?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.77,0:18:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.28,0:18:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that I love Kanata more \Nthan anyone else in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.91,0:18:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, that was it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.20,0:18:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really am no match for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.94,0:18:54.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Rookie Awards recipient \Ninformation:" "No awards given"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.94,0:18:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He accepts everything \Nabout me, good and bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.32,0:19:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He shows me everything \Nabout him, good and bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.87,0:19:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The place where I can feel most at ease,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.29,0:19:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the place that lets me be most at ease...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.46,0:19:20.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.30,0:19:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we're feeling nostalgic, \NI guess I'll go for another shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.13,0:19:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get another shoot with Yu-{\i1}chan {\i0}too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.13,0:19:30.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I regret a little that \NI can't be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.14,0:19:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough... I mean, \Nthat wasn't just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.68,0:19:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on... One more, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.67,0:19:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, you really bought that \Nas a hobby, didn't you?! Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.02,0:19:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.32,0:19:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to break it in before \NI went on a research trip...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.65,0:19:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, just like how you guys \Nare in my heart, Sou-{\i1}kun{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.32,0:19:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I continue to live in your hearts...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.04,0:19:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will continue to watch over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.21,0:19:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here goes! Okay, okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.29,0:19:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope that you guys, who gave me \Nmuch happiness, stay happy, Sou-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.72,0:20:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if they'll be surprised by this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.80,0:20:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, this photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.64,0:20:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like a human \Nshadow is in this photo...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.31,0:20:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A real ghost photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.77,0:20:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bath is open now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.40,0:20:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yu-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.40,0:20:17.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.29,0:20:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-L-Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.86,0:20:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.99,0:20:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to delete it! Delete it! It's cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.32,0:20:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Don't delete it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.28,0:20:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe instead of deleting it, we \Nshould cast it into a holy bonfire?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.04,0:20:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't throw it into a holy bonfire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.91,0:20:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that she's talking a bit, \Nthe way I see her has changed...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.59,0:20:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, I have the image \Nthat Minarin is a bit scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.05,0:20:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though she's actually really sweet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.16,0:20:46.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she's come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.98,0:20:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minami-{\i1}chan{\i0}, welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.97,0:20:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.89,0:20:53.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Those two really get along \Nwell with each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.89,0:20:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you were in charge of the class log today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.46,0:20:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was our teacher still \Nin the teacher's lounge?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.19,0:20:55.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.69,0:20:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yutaka... Your tie is crooked, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.23,0:20:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dear sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.77,0:21:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! I'm seeing friends \Nin this light again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.94,0:21:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'm feeling a bit tense.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.36,0:21:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.45,0:21:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3, 2, 1, okay... it's rolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.54,0:21:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, have you found him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.00,0:21:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he's not around? Anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.79,0:21:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't find the manager, either? \NHe's gotten away, dammit...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.79,0:21:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in either case, they're fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.15,0:21:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place, I thought that this show
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.15,0:21:24.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... it's rolling...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.26,0:21:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was somehow dangerous to \Nstart with, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.18,0:21:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had said no at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.22,0:21:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can't win against a political power,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.93,0:21:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or due to an adult's reasoning...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.47,0:21:32.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.68,0:21:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, it's rolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.89,0:21:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's rolling? Me, \Nor you, or the Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.15,0:21:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.31,0:21:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.98,0:21:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I've been saying, the camera is rolling...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.69,0:21:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.11,0:21:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isono! Isono! What is it, Nakajima?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.20,0:21:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, we'll have you listen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.99,0:21:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, we have a medley version!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.54,0:21:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1, 2, 3, 4!
